The paper proposes a new approach for learning Gaussian policies in reinforcement learning, which involves defining a smoothed version of the Q-value function. This makes it likely that the paper would be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with continuous control tasks, which suggests that it could be categorized under robotics (cs.RO) or systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of Hessian matrices, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV), making it a possible fifth category.
